        <num>CC 1522</num>
        <heading>1522.  Separate donations of usufruct and naked ownership</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1522.  Separate donations of usufruct and naked ownership
A disposition inter vivos or mortis causa by which the usufruct is given to one
person and the naked ownership to another is not a prohibited substitution.</p>
        </content>
